-- Pakistan Death Toll From Flash Floods in Northwest Rises to 526, Edhi Says
-- Anwar Shakir
-- 2010-07-31T07:15:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-31/pakistan-death-toll-from-flash-floods-in-northwest-rises-to-526-edhi-says.html

          
          
             Flash floods left 526 people dead
and thousands displaced after heavy rains in northwestern
Pakistan, according to the Edhi rescue service.  
 Peshawar, Charsadda, Kohat, Bannu and the tribal areas
bordering Afghanistan all are affected, Mujahid Khan, a
spokesman for Edhi, said by telephone from Peshawar today.  
